This article is a Presidential Memorandum from October 14, 2011, in which President Barack Obama certifies that the provision of U.S. drug interdiction assistance to the Government of Brazil is necessary due to the threat of illicit drug trafficking to Brazil's national security. The memorandum states that the interdiction of aircraft suspected of drug trafficking is necessary and that Brazil has appropriate procedures in place to protect against innocent loss of life during such interdiction. The Secretary of State is directed to publish this determination in the Federal Register and notify Congress.